[normal]Written evidence submitted by [bold]Aragon Housing Association[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]About the organisation[bold]GUHG comprises of 3 subsidiaries: Aragon Housing Association (Aragon), South Northants Homes (SNH) and Macintyre Housing Association (Macintyre).
[normal]The attached document 
[normal](Appendix 2
[normal]) sets out further details about GUHG.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Reason for submitting evidence[bold]We wish to give oral evidence to expand on this submission as the impact of Welfare Reform is complex and the nuances are difficult to convey in 3,000 words. We are also working on producing a report detailing the impact of the reforms six months after the introduction of the under-occupancy charge.  We would hope to present those findings to Select Committee. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Recommendations[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Executive s[bold]ummary of [bold]GUHG r[bold]esponse[bold]&#xa0;[bold]GUHG 
[normal]is working hard to support and encourage 
[normal]customers into employment and 
[normal]we 
[normal]welcome initiatives to further these aims. GUHG also welcome
[normal]s
[normal] any schemes for reducing under-
[normal]occupancy. However, 
[normal]Welfare Reform
[normal] do
[normal]es
[normal] not achieve either of
[normal] these for
[normal] customers in our area. 
[normal]Having examined our extensive data w
[normal]e are making this submission to report 
[normal]on 
[normal]the impact of Welfare Reform
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The impact of
[normal] Welfare Reform
[normal] is far reaching for 
[normal]all housing associations. We have reassessed our risks and revised our business plan.
[normal] The early indications are that rent arrears have gone up. Our customers are struggling 
[normal]to meet 
[normal]rising costs and are 
[normal]having to cut
[normal] back o
[normal]n fuel and food to make ends meet.
[normal] 
[normal] As a consequence our
[normal] referral
[normal]s for food parcels ha
[normal]ve
[normal] doubled.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Our 
[normal]opportunities to help customers downsize 
[normal]are 
[normal]limited by the 
[normal]lack of 
[normal]smaller social housing units. There is also a 
[normal]shortage
[normal] of 
[normal]appropriate 
[normal]housing in the private sector.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Overcrowding i
[normal]s not an issue in our area
[normal] and the
[normal] demand is for smaller housing units. 
[normal]Some
[normal] 
[normal]vacated 
[normal]three
[normal] bedroom
[normal]ed
[normal] properties are being 
[normal]allocated to
[normal] 
[normal]tenants with low needs because
[normal] households with higher needs 
[normal]no longer 
[normal]qualify for them
[normal]. 
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We are finding that t
[normal]he grant of 
[normal]Discretionary Housing Payment (
[normal]DHP
[normal])
[normal] by Local A
[normal]uthorities is masking the impact of 
[normal]Welfare Reform
[normal]. At the momen
[normal]t DHP is
[normal] a temporary provision 
[normal]and there is a dan
[normal]ger that any assessment by the Select C
[normal]ommittee will not 
[normal]accurately reflect 
[normal]the likely future impact.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We would be happy to assist the Select Committee and provide a full data report if this is required
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Our n[bold]ew and innov[bold]ative responses to the changes[bold]&#xa0;[bold]We have considered a number of innovative ways of assisting our customers to cope with the 
